HepG2 cells were culture in Dulbecco's Modified Eagle Medium (DMEM) supplemented with 10% fetal bovine serum (FBS), 50 units/mL penicillin and 50 µg/mL streptomycin. Cells were seed in 96-well plates (60,000 cells/well) and incubated for 24 h. The tested samples were diluted in serum free medium containing 25 µM 2′,7′, dichoroflouresceine diacetate (DCFH-DA, Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA, USA). The cells were wash with PBS and treated with test samples during 1 h. The medium containing tested samples was removed, ABAP (600 µM) was added and the plate was immediately placed on a Spectra Max plate reader for kinetic reading every 5 min during 1 h (37 ºC, emission at 538 nm and excitation at 485 nm). Quercetin (Sigma-Aldrich) was use as positive control. To calculate the percentage of decrease in oxidative stress, the Area Under the Curve (AUC) of fluorescence versus time was used.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
